In preparation for the upcoming Guatemalan general elections, Dr. Phil Gordon, National Security Advisor to the Vice President, held a virtual meeting with various civil society organizations in Guatemala involved in election observation. During the meeting, Dr. Gordon expressed the United States' support for free, fair, inclusive, and peaceful elections, as well as a transparent electoral process. Vice President Harris is leading the implementation of the U.S. Strategy to Address the Root Causes of Migration in Central America, which emphasizes democratic governance and support for civil society. The Vice President remains dedicated to strengthening these initiatives in northern Central America.